result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Ryan R. Newberry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Illegal Hunting Deer/Carcass, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 29.971(11).
  • Fail/Attach Ear Tag to Deer Carcass, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 29.347(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Defendant shall pay supervision fees as ordered by the Department of Corrections. 
If probation is ordered and ultimately revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used.

Defendant shall submit a DNA sample. Defendant shall issue an apology to the local sportsmen's club to be arranged by the Warden. Attend counseling as deemed appropriate by the probation agent. Revocation of all Chapter 29 privileges and approvals for 3 years on each count, consecutive. Forfeiture of the gun seized (.22 Rough Rider pistol).
Same conditions under Count 1 apply to this count as well. Revocation of all Chapter 29 privileges and approvals for 3 years on Count 2 is consecutive to Count 1.

Defendant Ryan R. Newberry in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement placed on the record by Atty. Tlusty. Advised of right to attorney. DE waived right to attorney. Court finds waiver of attorney given freely, voluntarily, and intelligently. DE enters a plea of guilty to counts 1, 2, 3, and 4. Plea colloquy. Court found plea given freely, voluntarily, and intelligently; accepted plea; found DE guilty; and ordered entry of JOC on counts 1 and 2. Brief comments by counsel and defendant. On Counts 1 and 2, Court withheld sentence and placed DE on probation for one year with the following conditions: $1,000.00 fine plus court costs on each count; DNA sample and surcharge; apology to the local sportsmen's club arranged through Warden; counseling as deemed appropriate by agent; revocation of all Chapter 29 privileges and approvals for 3 years on each count, consecutive; forfeiture of the gun seized (.22 Rough Rider pistol). On counts 3 and 4, pursuant to the agreement, the Court deferred entry of judgment of conviction for a period of one year and signs the order. Court dismissed but read in count 5. Court amended bond to allow travel outside the State of Wisconsin for business purposes. On tracking citations (16FO96, 16FO97, 16FO108), DE pleads no contest and court orders the forfeitures paid on those cases.
